Jerome Amerika allegedly murdered &amp; raped the 10-year-old in February. JOHANNESBURG - Judgment in the case against a man accused of killing a 10-year-old girl is expected today.Jerome Amerika allegedly murdered and raped Shamonique Claasen in February in Paarl.The court has heard emotional testimonies from relatives of the murdered 10-year-old. Amerika was in a relationship with the young victim's sister at the time of the attack.They have a three-year-old child together.Amerika has pleaded not guilty to rape and murder charges.The 10-year-old's body was found stuffed in a blanket, underneath a bed, in the room the accused slept in.(Edited by Shimoney Regter)